Name: Auto-Sequence AENUM
Intent: Auto-Sequence adverse event number

Name: Remove DEE KW
Intent: Remove DEE KW initially upon save at all times.

Name: Disable AENUM
Intent: Always disable adverse event number

Name: d+c IRBDATCB
Intent: When Not required is checked then disable + clear Date IRB informed.

Name: d+c UADE
Intent: If Did the event meet the definition of being serious? is not Yes then disable and clear Is the SAE considered a UADE?

Name: populate LTT
Intent: populate LLT

Name: d+c Seriousness checkboxes
Intent: If Did the event meet the definition of being serious? not Yes, then disable + clear all seriousness checkboxes.
Questions: SAE, SAEDTH, SAECNGL, SAEINTVN, SAEHOSP_PRLNG, SAEHOSP_NEW, SAEIMPR, SAELIFE

Name: h+c SAEADMDAT
Intent: If Resulted in new hospitalization (>24 hours) is not checked, then hide + clear Hospital admission and discharge dates.

Name: h+c AEENDAT
Intent: If Resolved and Resolved with sequelae and Death are not selected then hide + clear Date of resolution or death.

Name: h+c CAUSEDTH
Intent: If Outcome is not Death then hide + clear Primary cause of death.

Name: h+c SEQUELAE
Intent: If Outcome not Resolved with sequelae then hide + clear Specify sequelae.

Name: Disable DAYBTW1
Intent:
Always disable Number of days between
index procedure and event onset

Name: cf DAYBTW1
Intent: Calculate Number of days between index procedure and event onset

Name: Clear DAYBTW1
Intent:
If Date of event onset is missing, or if procedure date is missing, then clear Number of days between
index procedure and event onset.

Name: AQ+DM - SAEFET
Intent: If Did the event meet the definition of being serious? is Yes then at least one seriousness specification must be checked.
Message: Adverse Event meets the definition of being serious, at least one criteria must be checked.
Questions: SAE, SAEDTH, SAECNGL, SAEINTVN, SAEHOSP_PRLNG, SAEHOSP_NEW, SAEIMPR, SAELIFE
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <and>
            <equals>
                <question>SAE</question>
                <value>Yes</value>
            </equals>
            <not>
                <checked>
                    <question>SAEDTH</question>
                </checked>
            </not>
            <not>
                <checked>
                    <question>SAECNGL</question>
                </checked>
            </not>
            <not>
                <checked>
                    <question>SAEINTVN</question>
                </checked>
            </not>
            <not>
                <checked>
                    <question>SAEHOSP_PRLNG</question>
                </checked>
            </not>
            <not>
                <checked>
                    <question>SAEHOSP_NEW</question>
                </checked>
            </not>
            <not>
                <checked>
                    <question>SAEIMPR</question>
                </checked>
            </not>
            <not>
                <checked>
                    <question>SAELIFE</question>
                </checked>
            </not>
        </and>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <open_query>
            <query_status_open>14</query_status_open>
            <query_field>
                <question>SAELIFE</question>
            </query_field>
            <query_text>Adverse Event meets the definition of being serious, at least one criteria must be checked.</query_text>

        <message>

            <error_field>SAELIFE</error_field>
        </message>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

Name: CEC | CEC Status - Pending Adjudication
Intent: If all of the following keywords do not exist: 1) Final User Agreement 2) Final Chair Adjudication and current user's role is either: 1)CEC Adjudicator 2) CEC Chair, then set the CEC Status to Pending Adjudication on the current record.
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <and>
            <not>
                <exists>
                    <keyword_status_record>
                        <keyword>final_user_agreement</keyword>
                    </keyword_status_record>
                </exists>
            </not>
            <not>
                <exists>
                    <keyword_status_record>
                        <keyword>adj_cec_adjudication_config_chair_final</keyword>
                    </keyword_status_record>
                </exists>
            </not>
        </and>
        <or>
            <equals>
                <user_role/>
                <role>CEC Member</role>
            </equals>
            <equals>
                <user_role/>
                <role>CEC Chair</role>
            </equals>
        </or>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <set_cec_status>
            <cec_config>CEC Adjudication Config</cec_config>
            <cec_status>Pending Adjudication</cec_status>
            <cec_target>Current Record</cec_target>
        </set_cec_status>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

Name: CEC | CEC Status - Adjudicated
Intent: If EITHER of the following keywords exist: 1) Final User Agreement  2) Final Chair Adjudication AND current user's role is EITHER: 1) CEC Member 2) CEC Chair, then set the CEC Status to Adjudicated on the current record.

Message: Please verify field. Subjects must be older than 18 at the time of consent.
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <and>
            <lt>
                <question>AGE</question>
                <value>18</value>
            </lt>
        </and>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <open_query>
            <query_status_open>14</query_status_open>
            <query_field>
                <question>AGE</question>
            </query_field>
            <query_text>Please verify field. Subjects must be older than 18 at the time of consent.</query_text>
            <query_status_close>13</query_status_close>
        </open_query>
        <message>
            <message>Please verify field. Subjects must be older than 18 at the time of consent.</message>
            <error_field>AGE</error_field>
        </message>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

Name: Generated by CEC Configuration, disable save max record
Intent:
If all of the following:
- Record is NEW
- The number of existing Adjudication records are already at the expected max per CEC configuration
- The current user's role is not the role set as "Chair" per CEC configuration
then Disable Save and display message: "This record cannot be saved as the limit for the max number of Adjudication records for this event has been reached."
Message: This record cannot be saved as the limit for the max number of Adjudication records for this event has been reached.
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <and>
            <gte>
                <number_of_sibling_records>
                    <form>CEC Adjudication</form>
                </number_of_sibling_records>
                <value>2</value>
            </gte>
                            <not>
                    <equals>
                        <user_role />
                        <role>CEC Chair</role>
                    </equals>
                </not>
                        <equals>
                <new_record />
                <value>Yes</value>
            </equals>
        </and>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <disable_cec_save />
        <message>
            <message>This record cannot be saved as the limit for the max number of Adjudication records for this event has been reached.</message>
        </message>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

Name: Generated by CEC Chair Configuration, disable save
Intent: It will not allow any other Adjudication record to be saved (even cleaned up) if there is a Chair record for the AE.
Message: This record cannot be saved as the Chair Adjudication for this event has been completed.
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <or>
            <exists>
                <keyword_status_parent>
                    <keyword>adj_cec_adjudication_config_chair_in_progress</keyword>
                </keyword_status_parent>
            </exists>
            <exists>
                <keyword_status_parent>
                    <keyword>adj_cec_adjudication_config_chair_final</keyword>
                </keyword_status_parent>
            </exists>
        </or>
        <and>
            <not>
                <exists>
                    <keyword_status_record>
                        <keyword>adj_cec_adjudication_config_chair_in_progress</keyword>
                    </keyword_status_record>
                </exists>
            </not>

            <not>
                <exists>
                    <keyword_status_record>
                        <keyword>adj_cec_adjudication_config_chair_final</keyword>
                    </keyword_status_record>
                </exists>
            </not>
        </and>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <disable_save />
        <message>
            <message>This record cannot be saved as the Chair Adjudication for this event has been completed.</message>
        </message>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

Name: Hard Error
Intent: If Closed date is prior to Open date, trigger Hard error with message: Closed Date cannot be prior to Open Date. Please review.

    <Conditions>
        <and>
            <not>
                <blank>
                    <question>OPENDAT</question>
                </blank>
            </not>
            <not>
                <blank>
                    <question>CLOSDAT</question>
                </blank>
            </not>
            <lt>
                <question>CLOSDAT</question>
                <question>OPENDAT</question>

    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <message>
            <message>Closed Date cannot be prior to Open Date. Please review.</message>
            <error_field>CLOSDAT</error_field>

        </message>

</BusinessLogic>

Name: Hard Error
Intent: If Closed date is prior to Open date, trigger Hard error with message: Closed Date cannot be prior to Open Date. Please review.
Message: Closed Date cannot be prior to Open Date. Please review.
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <and>
            <not>
                <blank>
                    <question>OPENDAT</question>
                </blank>
            </not>
            <not>
                <blank>
                    <question>CLOSDAT</question>
                </blank>
            </not>
            <lt>
                <question>CLOSDAT</question>
                <question>OPENDAT</question>
                <utctime>1</utctime>
            </lt>
        </and>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <message>
            <message>Closed Date cannot be prior to Open Date. Please review.</message>
            <error_field>CLOSDAT</error_field>
            <hard_edit/>
        </message>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

Name: Hard Error
Intent: If End Date is prior to Start date, trigger Hard error with message: End Date cannot be prior to Start Date. Please review.
Message: End Date cannot be prior to Start Date. Please review.
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <and>
            <not>
                <blank>
                    <question>SOV</question>
                </blank>
            </not>
            <not>
                <blank>
                    <question>EOV</question>
                </blank>
            </not>
            <lt>
                <question>EOV</question>
                <question>SOV</question>
                <utctime>1</utctime>
            </lt>
        </and>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <message>
            <message>End Date cannot be prior to Start Date. Please review.</message>
            <error_field>EOV</error_field>
            <hard_edit/>
        </message>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

Name: Calculate EQ5D5L01

<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>

                </blank>
            </not>
        </and>

                        </then>
                    </when>
                    <when>
                        <value>I have slight problems walking</value>
                        <then>

                        </then>
                    </when>

                        <then>

                        </then>

                    <when>
                        <value>I am unable to walk</value>
                        <then>
                            <value>5</value>
                        </then>
                    </when>
                    <when>
                        <value>Missing value</value>
                        <then>
                            <value>9</value>

Name: AQ+DM -  ELIGIBLE No
Intent: If Does the subject meet all eligibility criteria? is No then auto-query and display message: The subject is not eligible to be enrolled in the study.
Message: The subject is not eligible to be enrolled in the study.
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <and>
            <equals>
                <question>ELIGIBLE</question>
                <value>No</value>
            </equals>
        </and>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <open_query>
            <query_status_open>14</query_status_open>
            <query_field>
                <question>ELIGIBLE</question>
            </query_field>
            <query_text>The subject is not eligible to be enrolled in the study.</query_text>
            <query_status_close>13</query_status_close>
        </open_query>
        <message>
            <message>The subject is not eligible to be enrolled in the study.</message>
            <error_field>ELIGIBLE</error_field>
        </message>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

Name: Hard Error EOV
Intent: If End Date is prior to Start date, trigger Hard error with message: End Date cannot be prior to Start Date. Please review.
Message: End Date cannot be prior to Start Date. Please review.
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <and>
            <not>
                <blank>
                    <question>SOV</question>
                </blank>
            </not>
            <not>
                <blank>
                    <question>EOV</question>
                </blank>
            </not>
            <lt>
                <question>EOV</question>
                <question>SOV</question>
                <utctime>1</utctime>
            </lt>
        </and>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <message>
            <message>End Date cannot be prior to Start Date. Please review.</message>
            <error_field>EOV</error_field>
            <hard_edit />
        </message>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

Name: Hard Error
Intent: If Last date of visit is prior to First date of visit , trigger Hard error with message: Last Date cannot be prior to First Date. Please review.
Message: Last Date cannot be prior to First Date. Please review.
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <and>
            <not>
                <blank>
                    <question>FIRSTDOV</question>
                </blank>
            </not>
            <not>
                <blank>
                    <question>LASTDOV</question>
                </blank>
            </not>
            <lt>
                <question>LASTDOV</question>
                <question>FIRSTDOV</question>
                <utctime>1</utctime>
            </lt>
        </and>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <message>
            <message>Last Date cannot be prior to First Date. Please review.</message>
            <error_field>LASTDOV</error_field>
            <hard_edit />
        </message>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

Name: Trigger Record Interim Monitoring
Intent: If the Visit Type = Interim, Trigger the Interim Monitoring Visit form and display the following message: Please use the link provided here to record the Interim Monitoring Visit details. The link will appear upon save of the Monitoring Visit Log.
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <and>
            <equals>
                <question>VISITTYPE</question>
                <value>Interim</value>
            </equals>
        </and>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <trigger_record>
            <trigger_record_message>Please use the link provided here to record the Interim Monitoring Visit details. The link will appear upon save of the Monitoring Visit Log.</trigger_record_message>
            <trigger_record_code>Interim Monitoring Visit</trigger_record_code>
            <trigger_record_field>
                <question>VISITTYPE</question>
            </trigger_record_field>
            <trigger_record_form>
                <form>Interim Monitoring Visit</form>
            </trigger_record_form>
            <trigger_record_relationship>3</trigger_record_relationship>
            <trigger_record_number_of_records>1</trigger_record_number_of_records>
        </trigger_record>
        <set_keyword>
            <keyword>data_entry_error</keyword>
            <target>
                <record />
            </target>
        </set_keyword>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

Name: AQ IBILICS
Intent: If IBILICS is clinically significant, then auto query: Please enter this clinically significant value on an Adverse Event CRF.
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <and>
            <equals>
                <question>IBILICS</question>
                <value>Yes</value>
            </equals>
        </and>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <open_query>
            <query_status_open>14</query_status_open>
            <query_field>
                <question>IBILICS</question>
            </query_field>
            <query_text>Please enter this clinically significant value on an Adverse Event CRF.</query_text>
            <query_status_close>13</query_status_close>
        </open_query>
        <set_keyword>
            <keyword>data_entry_error</keyword>
            <target>
                <record />
            </target>
        </set_keyword>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

        <set_keyword>

</BusinessLogic>

Questions: CNST, SRCDOC, CRF, INCEXC, PE, MDHX, MDHXCONMED, VITALS, RVWVITALS, LABSPEC, AEINQ, AESAE, ADMINIP, IPACCNT, REGDOC, ADMINST, OTHER

                <checked>
                    <question>INCEXC</question>
                </checked>
            </not>
            <not>
                <checked>

                </checked>
            </not>
            <not>
                <checked>

                </checked>
            </not>
            <not>

                </checked>
            </not>
            <not>
                <checked>

                </checked>

            <not>

Name: DM SDLINIT
Intent: Evaluate Initials.  If not in correct format, display message: The initials you entered are not in the correct format. Please make sure the subject initials are capital letters and are in the format "ABC", or "A-C" if no middle initial is known.
Message: The subject initials you entered are not in the correct format. Please make sure the subject initials are capital letters and are in the format "ABC", or "A-C" if no middle initial is known.
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <and>
            <not>
                <like>
                    <question>SDLINIT</question>
                    <value>[A-Z][A-Z][A-Z]</value>
                </like>
            </not>
            <not>
                <like>
                    <question>SDLINIT</question>
                    <value>[A-Z]-[A-Z]</value>
                </like>
            </not>
            <not>
                <blank>
                    <question>SDLINIT</question>
                </blank>
            </not>
        </and>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <message>
            <message>The subject initials you entered are not in the correct format. Please make sure the subject initials are capital letters and are in the format "ABC", or "A-C" if no middle initial is known.</message>
            <error_field>SDLINIT</error_field>
            <hard_edit/>
        </message>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

            <message>Stop time must be on or after Start time. Please correct.</message>

        </message>

Name: No New Records Created - Other (hard)
Intent: ALL PATIENT-TYPE RECORDS - If data entry is marked as "Complete" within the Study Exit record, disable save & display message: "Within the Study Exit record, *Is Data Entry for this patient complete?* is indicated as Yes.  No further record creation is allowed unless this value is changed."
Message: Within the Study Exit record, *Is Data Entry for this patient complete?* is indicated as Yes.  No further record creation is allowed unless this value is changed.
Workflow Forms: AE, AEACTEL, BSL, DEVDEF, DEVINFO, DC, PROC, DV, REG, DS, IE
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <and>
            <exists>
                <keyword_status_patient>
                    <keyword>data_entry_complete</keyword>
                </keyword_status_patient>
            </exists>
            <equals>
                <new_record/>
                <value>Yes</value>
            </equals>
        </and>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <disable_save/>
        <message>
            <message>Within the Study Exit record, *Is Data Entry for this patient complete?* is indicated as Yes. No further record creation is allowed unless this value is changed.</message>
            <hard_edit/>
        </message>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

Name: CEC Adjudication - Record Incomplete
Intent: AUTOGENERATED - Record Incomplete
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <or>
            <exists>
                <keyword_status_record>
                    <keyword>data_entry_error</keyword>
                </keyword_status_record>
            </exists>
            <exists>
                <keyword_status_child_log_record>
                    <keyword>data_entry_error</keyword>
                </keyword_status_child_log_record>
            </exists>
            <exists>
                <query_status_record_cel>
                    <query_state>open</query_state>
                    <query_type>4</query_type>
                    <query_status>14</query_status>
                </query_status_record_cel>
            </exists>
        </or>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <set_record_status>
            <record_status>Record Incomplete</record_status>
        </set_record_status>
        <suppress_esig>
            <esignature>CEC Member Signed</esignature>
        </suppress_esig>
        <invalidate_esig>
            <esignature>CEC Member Signed</esignature>
            <target>
                <record />
            </target>
        </invalidate_esig>
        <suppress_esig>
            <esignature>Adjudication Complete</esignature>
        </suppress_esig>
        <invalidate_esig>
            <esignature>Adjudication Complete</esignature>
            <target>
                <record />
            </target>
        </invalidate_esig>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

Name: Site Logs - Disable the Save Button and Lock the Record
Intent: AUTOGENERATED - Lock the Record if the Current Record Status is any of the following.
Message: This form has had the save button disabled and cannot be edited.
Logic:
<BusinessLogic>
    <Conditions>
        <or>
            <equals>
                <current_record_status />
                <value>Record Locked</value>
            </equals>
        </or>
    </Conditions>
    <Actions>
        <disable_save />
        <message>
            <message>This form has had the save button disabled and cannot be edited.</message>
        </message>
    </Actions>
</BusinessLogic>

Name: GLOSSARY
Intent:
KW = Keyword. These are used to flag data conditions for other BLs or reports to use later.
RS = Record Status. These are the icons that represent the current record status. These can be used for report filtration.  Only one can be present on the current record at any given time.
PS = Patient Status. These are the icons that represent the current patient/subject status. These can be used for report filtration.  Only one can be present on the current patient at any given time.
ALL PATIENT-TYPE RECORDS = When you see this in a Workflow BL Intention, please select ONLY records from the Form Manager application that are of the type "patient".
ALL RECORDS = When you see this in a Workflow BL Intention, simply select ALL records from the Form Manager application, with the exception of any form designs that are designated as "Catalog".
PRIMARY = Records that are intended to go through the study approval workflow. NOT Records which reside in an CEL. When you see this, slow down, and carefully select ONLY the form designs that are meant to achieve an approval.
GRID RECORDS = Forms that exist within a dynamic grid on the Patient Record Page. These do NOT include CELs on the parent forms. When you see this, slow down, and carefully select ONLY the form designs that exist within the associated grid in Interval Manager.
EL = An Embedded Log is an object that can be added to a form design that can either display CEL or Primary records. The EL concept is to create a click to add data entry scenario of a specific dataset when viewing another record.  See below for CEL and IEL.
CEL = Child Embedded Log. A type of EL that can allow the user to create related records from the current record while maintaining a direct relationship through the dataset, where the child will always call-out the parent record_id from where it was created. A good example of this might be a CEL that resides within a Procedure Form. The CEL might be the ability to add Stent Information related to the Procedure. These CEL records will now only be able to be viewed in this context as a log record/row within the Procedure form. The CEL records will reference the parent record_id within the CEL dataset. The CEL Stent records will be able to affect the parent Procedure record status. CEL records will typically NOT be a part of the approval process as they will be considered part of a semblance of a collective whole (in the Procedure record).
IEL = Independent Embedded Log. A type of Log that allows data entry of another record that is UNRELATED to the record which the Log is displaying within. Records used in IELs are typically expected to go through the approval process. Any record (row) of the Log will NOT have a reference to the record it is displaying within as a log row. Records the are included in an IEL can be viewed outside of the IEL if a user has access to a link from a report, in which case, the user will be taken to that record only, and not the Log format.
LOG HOLDER = Placeholder record that displays an Independent Embedded Log (IEL) for the end user.  The log record here achieves a blue record status and does not go through the record workflow where the PRIMARY records within the IEL typically would.
BL TRIGGERED RECORDS = This is a reference to records that are set within a manually created Form BL to trigger for example, a Protocol Deviation record for completion.
EMAIL - This is in any BL name or intent that triggers an Email Notification or is related to the Email Notification trigger criteria.
PVI - Populate Visit Interval.
CATALOG = A catalog is a form design used for Inventory or a true lookup type catalog & is NOT a data entry record.  These are outside the scope of record workflow.
"Form" vs "Record" terminology = A "Form" is design mode. A "Form" becomes a "Record" when used in data entry. In other words, a Designer will create a form for a study. A Data Entry user will have "Forms" available to them. A saved "Form" becomes a "Record".  For support, or troubleshooting, it is advantageous to distinguish between the two for the sake of clarity.

Name: CEC | KW - Clear Action Keywords
Intent: At all times, clear all 'action' keywords from the current record (CEC Required Action, CEC Not Required Action).
